FBIS3-54389 "drnes017_a_94011" FBIS-NES-94-017 Document Type:Daily Report 26 Jan 1994 ARAB AFRICA Algeria Bouteflika Turns Down Offer of Presidency NC2601111594 Paris AFP in English 1056 GMT 26 Jan 94 NC2601111594 Paris AFP Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Algiers, Jan 26 (AFP) -- Algerian former foreign minister Abdelaziz Bouteflika has turned down a proposal to become the country's president for a three-year transitional period, an official spokesman said Wednesday [26 Jan]. Bouteflika, 59, who served under the 1965-78 presidency of Houari Boumediene, had been mooted as the man most likely to take up the post, with the approval of the armed forces. Abdelkadar Bensalah, spokesman for a national conference organised by the government but boycotted by all the main political parties, announced that the gathering, meeting for the second and final day, "has been informed of this refusal."
